            "name": "Is Varanasi safe at night for solo women?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Main ghats see decent foot traffic till about 9 p.m.; after that, stick to lit roads or a prepaid cab."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Can I wear jeans in Varanasi?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Yes—pair them with a hip-length tunic or kurta to keep knees & hips discreet."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Are there female-only dorms in Varanasi?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "GoStops & Zostel both offer 4- to 6-bed female dorms; book early in peak months."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How to avoid scams in Varanasi?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Decline unsolicited guiding offers, fix boat prices in advance, and use official temple counters for donations."
            }
          }
        ]
